>> source: https://www.traderjoes.com/home/recipes/iced-chai-latte
>> serves: 2
>> total time: 15 minutes

To make whipped cream: In a #large bowl{}, with a #hand mixer or stand mixer{} combine: 1/2 cup @heavy cream{1/2%cup}, 2 teaspoons @TJ's Spicy Chai Tea Latte Mix{2%tsp} and 1 teaspoon @Bourbon Vanilla Extract{1%tsp}. Whip until stiff peaks form, about ~{4%minutes}. Set aside.

To make chai iced latte: In a #medium-sized pitcher{}, whisk together 6 tablespoons @TJ's Spicy Chai Tea Latte Mix{6%Tbsp} and 1/2 cup @hot water{1/2%cup} until mix completely dissolves. Add 1 cup @TJ's Cold Brew Coffee Concentrate{1%cup} to pitcher and stir until combined. Serve chilled or pour over ice (we recommend making your own cold brew ice cubes), then top with reserved whipped cream.
